{"word":"H1471 - גֹּוי - gôwy - go'-ee - Gentile","slug":"H1471","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">גֹּוי</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>gôwy"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>go'-ee"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Gentile"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D2;&#x05BC;&#x05D9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D2;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05D9; - go&#x0302;y  go&#x0302;y</b> - <i>go'ee, go'-ee</i><p/>Apparently from the same root as <a href=\"#/H1465\">H1465</a> (in the sense of <i>massing</i>); a foreign <i>nation</i>; hence a <i>Gentile</i>; also (figuratively) a <i>troop</i> of animals, or a <i>flight</i> of locusts: - Gentile, heathen, nation, people."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1468\">H1468</a>, <a href=\"#/H1470\">H1470</a>, <a href=\"#/H1474\">H1474</a>"}]}